History:
    - 2022-May-18: Written, FIS

Description:
    - This 00README file describes how the "models_arch-opt-mse-sig2_thrs-opt-mse-sig2" case was designed.

Procedure (followed for each output):
    - Threshold (optimized threshold for each output). Method:
        Analysis folder: "notebooks_SHERPA_thrs_optimization_per_output"
        Script: "Create_optimized_threshold_dict.ipynb"
        Config:
            SHE_alg    = 'GridSearch'
            method     = 'sig' # 'sig'; 'aic'
            sig        = 2
            pdf        = True # Quantile-based threshold
            
            ## Explore optimal quantile-thrs per output
            SHE_path   = f'./hyperparameter_tuning_{SHE_alg}_threshold_SHERPA/'
            SHE_date   = '2022041[6,7]_*'
    
    - Architecture optimized using SHERPA as follows:
    
        Analysis folder: "notebooks_evaluate_SHERPA_cases_loss-mse"
        Script: loss_vs_complexity_SHERPA_study.ipynb
        Config: 
            SHE_alg    = 'GridSearch'
            method     = 'sig'
            sig        = 2

            ## Explore optimal num. of hidden layers and num. of nodes (per layer) with quantile-thrs per output
            SHE_path   = f'./hyperparameter_tuning_optimized-threshold-per-output_{SHE_alg}_SHERPA/'
            SHE_date   = '2022051[4,5]_*'
            
        * Note that the arch-opt is then used for SingleNNs.